  "outcome": "Creates a CHED-PP pre-notification end-to-end for a non-Article-72 country of origin (NO) and commodity 06011010, choosing manual entry and adding the commodity via code search, selecting 'Internal market' as the reason for import, then returning to the Notification Hub task list to complete bulk commodity details, additional details, transport to the BCP (CONPNT/INSPBAR1, plane), goods movement answers (No/No), contacts, a phytosanitary certificate with an attached file, and a newly created consignor/exporter with the consignee copied via 'Same as consignee' — then accepts the declaration, submits, captures reference CHEDPP.GB.2026.1525991 from the Initial risk assessment page, and confirms the CHED status tag renders in the BCP decision app search.",
  "pageNamingBasis": "Every pageGuess is taken from the h1 of the accessibility snapshot at the stated action id, not inferred from the URL.",
  "notes": [
    "Non-Article-72 variant: after selecting 'Internal market' as the reason for import, no Article 72 / phytosanitary-exemption questions were presented — the journey went straight to the Notification Hub.",
    "The journey is NOT a linear wizard. After the reason-for-import page (page-5) the app returns to a 'Notification Hub' task-list at /overview (action 23), from which the Commodity section is re-entered. This is the key architectural shape of the IPAFFS CHED-PP flow.",
    "The trace's network log is shared across several tests in the spec file (4241 requests, 15 pages; draft ids DRAFT.GB.2026.1525736 and DRAFT.GB.2026.1525737 belong to OTHER tests). This run's own draft is DRAFT.GB.2026.1525991, confirmed from in-page hrefs read out of the snapshot at action 34. URLs below are the route shapes for this run's draft.",
    "The page <title> and the <h1> disagree on the origin page: title is 'Origin of the animal or product' (generic across CHED types) while the h1 is CHED-PP specific — 'Origin of the plants, plant product or other objects'. Recorded the h1.",
    "Two distinct pages both render h1 'Commodity' (the code-search/selection pages at consignment/page-3+page-4, and the bulk-details page at commodity/details/bulk). Disambiguated in pageGuess.",
    "Date fields are three-part Day/Month/Year GOV.UK date inputs; the BCP arrival page adds Hour/Minutes.",
    "Actions 80-82 (Get cookies, Attach 'notification-id', Attach 'notification-details') are test-harness noise and are omitted."
